1. Đavo je često opisan kao *demon* u srpskim pričama. (The devil is often described as a *demon* in Serbian stories.)
2. Zastrašujući *demon* je uplašio decu u parku. (The terrifying *demon* scared children in the park.)
3. Sveti Vasilije je navodno bio u stanju da tera *demone*. (Saint Basil was supposedly able to drive out *demons*.)
4. Njegovo ponašanje se promenilo, postao je *demon* u kuhinji. (His behavior changed, he became a *demon* in the kitchen.)
5. Svi u selu su verovali da je šuma puna *demona*. (Everyone in the village believed that the forest was full of *demons*.)
6. Postoje mnoge verzije priča o *demonima*, ali niko ne zna da li su istinite. (There are many versions of stories about *demons*, but no one knows if they are true.)
7. Ako među nama ima *demona*, neka se pokažu sada! (If there are any *demons* among us, let them show themselves now!)
8. U većini religija, *demoni* su prikazani kao zli duhovi. (In most religions, *demons* are depicted as evil spirits.)
9. Često sanjam o *demonima* koji me progone. (I often dream about *demons* chasing me.)
10. On je imao reputaciju *demona* u krevetu. (He had a reputation as a *demon* in bed.)